						<summary>

						

						<p>On a pillar in the ‘temple of heroes’ (Vīrula-guḍi).</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Śaka 1346, Krōdhi Kārttika •• 10, Thursday = 1424 A.D., November 2, if the tithi was śukla, or November 16, if the tithi was bahula.</hi></p>						

						<p>It records the installation of a Nandi image and a <hi rend="italic">garuḍa-stambha</hi> set up by Chavu[lāśu]la Vīriseṭi, in the presence of Anuṁgu-maṁḍalēśvara who bore the titles <hi rend="italic">mahāmaṇḍalēśvara</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Ayōdhyāpuravarēśvara.</hi></p>						

						</summary>
